1
00:00:00,192 --> 00:00:03,570
(speaking Chinese)

2
00:00:03,654 --> 00:00:06,740
Oh Su Lin, we've been looking
for you all these weeks.

3
00:00:06,823 --> 00:00:09,409
Mr. Williams needs your
help so desperately.

4
00:00:09,493 --> 00:00:10,452
I cannot help.

5
00:00:10,536 --> 00:00:12,663
You must forget that you found Su Lin.

6
00:00:12,746 --> 00:00:15,249
Forget it?
But you're his only witness!

7
00:00:15,332 --> 00:00:16,583
You're the only one that can help!

8
00:00:16,667 --> 00:00:19,253
Not as a witness, only with silence
can I repay

9
00:00:19,336 --> 00:00:22,464
his great kindness to me
and my family in China.

10
00:00:22,548 --> 00:00:23,298
Why?

11
00:00:23,382 --> 00:00:25,968
I heard other things
that most unhappy day

12
00:00:26,051 --> 00:00:27,636
from Mrs. Williams' bedroom.

13
00:00:27,719 --> 00:00:29,680
His voice very loud and angry.

14
00:00:29,763 --> 00:00:31,473
A flower bases broken to pieces.

15
00:00:31,557 --> 00:00:33,600
He can explain all that.

16
00:00:33,684 --> 00:00:35,894
They do not believe
what he's already told,

17
00:00:35,978 --> 00:00:40,566
that I heard anything would
do harm. Don't you see?

18
00:00:45,696 --> 00:00:46,530
Yes.

19
00:00:49,449 --> 00:00:53,287
Much sorrow comes from women
who know not honor and truth.

20
00:00:53,370 --> 00:00:55,706
And Mrs. Williams, she's not true.

21
00:00:55,789 --> 00:00:57,416
Even to that Torrence man.

22
00:00:58,667 --> 00:01:00,210
What makes you say that?

23
00:01:00,294 --> 00:01:02,963
That night when he was
killed, her sickness was but

24
00:01:03,046 --> 00:01:05,465
wall of falsehood behind
which she could go secretly

25
00:01:05,549 --> 00:01:07,593
to a meeting place.

26
00:01:08,552 --> 00:01:12,055
You... you mean
she went out that night?

27
00:01:14,933 --> 00:01:18,103
Su Lin, are you sure?

28
00:01:18,186 --> 00:01:20,480
Yes, because next morning
in her bedroom

29
00:01:20,564 --> 00:01:22,858
I found street shoes
that had been worn.

30
00:01:22,941 --> 00:01:25,277
Her coat on the closet
floor with the sleeves

31
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:28,238
turned inside out
as though removed hurriedly,

32
00:01:28,322 --> 00:01:30,949
and in one pocket a door key
to some hotel.

33
00:01:31,033 --> 00:01:33,368
Su Lin! That's it!

34
00:01:33,452 --> 00:01:35,662
Proof that she and Torrence
had planned to meet that night

35
00:01:35,746 --> 00:01:39,291
after he killed Mr. Williams.
What hotel was it?

36
00:01:39,374 --> 00:01:43,754
Oh, I... I don't remember.

37
00:01:43,837 --> 00:01:47,466
The key, what did you do with it?

38
00:01:47,549 --> 00:01:49,259
Returned to coat pocket.

39
00:01:49,343 --> 00:01:52,054
Come on,
we'll get to Lieutenant Quincy.

40
00:01:52,137 --> 00:01:53,180
He'll know what to do.

41
00:01:53,263 --> 00:01:55,599
And pray, Su Lin,
every step of the way.

42
00:02:03,106 --> 00:02:04,399
Now hold everything.

43
00:02:04,483 --> 00:02:06,485
Even if this long shot don't work out,

44
00:02:06,568 --> 00:02:07,986
we'll just keep on pitching.

45
00:02:11,573 --> 00:02:14,576
(speaking Chinese)

46
00:02:21,333 --> 00:02:22,959
Here it is. Yes.

47
00:02:23,043 --> 00:02:26,088
Room 302. Airport Hotel, Oakland.

48
00:02:26,171 --> 00:02:27,756
Maybe we got our miracle!

49
00:02:27,839 --> 00:02:29,007
A special little Chinese one.

50
00:02:29,091 --> 00:02:31,176
It is the hope that
Su Lin was a small help

51
00:02:31,259 --> 00:02:32,010
to Mr. William.

52
00:02:32,094 --> 00:02:32,844
Oh, Su Lin!

53
00:02:32,928 --> 00:02:34,471
Come on. Next stop, Oakland.

54
00:02:34,554 --> 00:02:36,765
I sense a little ladies
Hotel Rendezvous.

55
00:02:38,642 --> 00:02:39,810
I was on night duty then,
all right.

56
00:02:39,893 --> 00:02:41,687
But I sure don't remember
a looker like this.

57
00:02:41,770 --> 00:02:42,521
Quite a dish, eh?

58
00:02:42,604 --> 00:02:45,315
A little two highly seasoned
for my digestion, thanks.

59
00:02:45,399 --> 00:02:46,316
Lieutenant.

60
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:49,695
Just found a couple of cards
for room 302 on June 9th.

61
00:02:49,778 --> 00:02:52,489
Judge Baxter checked out at noon.

62
00:02:52,572 --> 00:02:57,119
Mr. And Mrs. J Burns.
Room not slept in.

63
00:02:57,202 --> 00:02:59,955
J Burns, Burns.

64
00:03:01,915 --> 00:03:05,168
Look Quincy, the handwriting
on the card is identical

65
00:03:05,252 --> 00:03:06,211
to that on the photograph.

66
00:03:06,294 --> 00:03:07,713
And here's a little
more of the same thing.

67
00:03:07,796 --> 00:03:09,631
The coverup telegram to Aunt Margaret.

68
00:03:09,715 --> 00:03:11,341
And look at the impressions.

69
00:03:11,425 --> 00:03:13,677
Jay here and here, RNS.

70
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:17,764
J Burns, that's the name
she started a telegram too.

71
00:03:17,848 --> 00:03:19,683
Room not slept in.

72
00:03:19,766 --> 00:03:21,518
Say I got that dame
pegged now, Lieutenant,

73
00:03:21,601 --> 00:03:23,353
she said they'd be out
of the room by midnight

74
00:03:23,437 --> 00:03:25,230
as her husband was catching a plane.

75
00:03:31,445 --> 00:03:32,279
But Quincy,

76
00:03:33,321 --> 00:03:35,073
this ties it all up, doesn't it?

77
00:03:35,157 --> 00:03:36,616
Yeah, like a greased pig.

78
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:38,869
What do you mean? We've got
the evidence now, the proof.

79
00:03:38,952 --> 00:03:39,703
Of what?

80
00:03:39,786 --> 00:03:42,372
Su Lin's theory that Irene
was playing the field?

81
00:03:42,456 --> 00:03:44,082
This evidence only proves
that she came here

82
00:03:44,166 --> 00:03:46,168
to keep a date
with a man named Burns.

83
00:03:46,251 --> 00:03:48,128
We can't even prove that
he didn't keep the date.

84
00:03:48,211 --> 00:03:50,130
But you know he didn't,
there wasn't any Burns.

85
00:03:50,213 --> 00:03:52,424
It was only a name that
she and Torrence used!

86
00:03:52,507 --> 00:03:54,092
Fine, if you can prove that

87
00:03:54,176 --> 00:03:57,721
Williams will be free, but
none of this will prove it.

88
00:03:57,804 --> 00:04:00,682
Sorry copper, but we are
just up another blind alley.

89
00:04:00,766 --> 00:04:01,933
-Wait!
-Yes sir?

90
00:04:02,017 --> 00:04:04,269
There's a couple of sample
cases from Mr. Sam Andrews.

91
00:04:04,352 --> 00:04:05,520
Came up from the station this morning.

92
00:04:05,604 --> 00:04:06,480
Take them to Parlor B right away.

93
00:04:06,563 --> 00:04:07,481
Sure thing, sir.

94
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:27,751
(bangs gavel)

95
00:04:27,834 --> 00:04:29,503
Be seated.

96
00:04:29,586 --> 00:04:31,630
Case of the state
versus Walter Williams.

97
00:04:31,713 --> 00:04:33,048
Proceed, Mr. Eldridge.

98
00:04:34,257 --> 00:04:37,677
Your Honor, we will
call Mrs. Irene Williams.

99
00:04:40,180 --> 00:04:41,723
Take the stand Mrs. Williams.

100
00:04:51,650 --> 00:04:53,026
Raise your right hand.

101
00:04:53,109 --> 00:04:54,736
Do you solemnly swear the
testimony you're about

102
00:04:54,820 --> 00:04:56,071
to give in this cause to be
the truth, the whole truth,

103
00:04:56,154 --> 00:04:57,948
and nothing but the truth,
so help you God?

104
00:04:58,031 --> 00:04:59,282
I do.

105
00:05:00,784 --> 00:05:02,911
-What cooks?
-The defense call on her?

106
00:05:04,704 --> 00:05:07,749
Mr. Eldridge, what's the
purpose in calling this witness?

107
00:05:07,833 --> 00:05:10,961
Merely for purposes of
identifying handwriting.

108
00:05:11,044 --> 00:05:15,715
Now, Mrs. Williams, this
photograph of you...

109
00:05:15,799 --> 00:05:17,217
Was stolen from my apartment.

110
00:05:17,300 --> 00:05:19,261
So, according to the inscription,

111
00:05:19,344 --> 00:05:22,389
"to Walt, my adoring and
adored husband, Irene,"

112
00:05:22,472 --> 00:05:23,932
this belongs to Mr. Williams.

113
00:05:24,015 --> 00:05:26,685
This is your handwriting, isn't it?

114
00:05:26,768 --> 00:05:27,811
Of course.

115
00:05:27,894 --> 00:05:30,981
I'm touched that he should
have wanted it so badly.

116
00:05:31,064 --> 00:05:35,193
And this telegram addressed
to Mrs. Margaret Hubbard.

117
00:05:35,277 --> 00:05:36,778
Is that also your handwriting?

118
00:05:38,029 --> 00:05:38,864
It is.

119
00:05:45,453 --> 00:05:48,582
Now Mrs. Burns, I mean, Mrs. Williams,

120
00:05:49,875 --> 00:05:50,625
This photograph is inscribed,

121
00:05:50,709 --> 00:05:54,713
"to Jim, my adoring and adored, Irene."

122
00:05:54,796 --> 00:05:55,547
Did you write this too?

123
00:05:55,630 --> 00:05:57,465
I... I see no point in all this.

124
00:05:57,549 --> 00:05:59,551
Merely answer counsel's questions.

125
00:05:59,634 --> 00:06:03,638
-Did you write it?
-I did.

126
00:06:03,722 --> 00:06:05,599
And these letters addressed
to Mr. James Torrence...

127
00:06:05,682 --> 00:06:07,017
-did you write them?
-Yes.

128
00:06:14,649 --> 00:06:17,277
And this monogrammed garment,

129
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:18,695
a gift from you to Mr. Torrence?

130
00:06:18,778 --> 00:06:21,031
Why must I be tortured
again by all this?

131
00:06:21,114 --> 00:06:23,783
I never made any secret of
my love for Jim Torrence.

132
00:06:23,867 --> 00:06:25,118
That's why he is dead.

133
00:06:25,201 --> 00:06:26,912
Your love for Jim Torrance?

134
00:06:26,995 --> 00:06:28,204
Yet on the very night he was killed,

135
00:06:28,288 --> 00:06:30,749
you had a rendezvous with a
man named Burns, didn't you?

136
00:06:30,832 --> 00:06:32,083
I don't know what
you're talking about.

137
00:06:32,167 --> 00:06:33,585
I don't know any man named Burns.

138
00:06:33,668 --> 00:06:35,587
I was at home that night, very ill.

139
00:06:35,670 --> 00:06:37,297
Oh yes, the sleeping pills.

140
00:06:37,380 --> 00:06:38,882
Well, you must walk
in your sleep then,

141
00:06:38,965 --> 00:06:40,675
for you spent at least
part of that night

142
00:06:40,759 --> 00:06:42,344
at the airport hotel in Oakland,

143
00:06:42,427 --> 00:06:45,013
where you registered for
Mr. and Mrs. J Burns.

144
00:06:45,096 --> 00:06:46,765
Don't waste the court's time
trying to deny it.

145
00:06:46,848 --> 00:06:51,311
This is the registration card
that you signed at 9:20 PM,

146
00:06:51,394 --> 00:06:56,399
and there's the room clerk
who assigned you to room 302.

147
00:06:56,650 --> 00:07:00,695
And this Mrs. Williams
is the key to room 302,

148
00:07:00,779 --> 00:07:03,406
which you very carelessly
left in the pocket of a coat,

149
00:07:03,490 --> 00:07:05,116
which was found
in your closet yesterday.

150
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:07,702
All right. I was there.
Now are you satisfied?

151
00:07:07,786 --> 00:07:09,287
Not quite.

152
00:07:09,371 --> 00:07:12,624
This Jay Burns, Mrs. Williams.
Was his first name Jack?

153
00:07:12,707 --> 00:07:13,708
Yes.

154
00:07:13,792 --> 00:07:15,126
Have you been in
contact with him lately?

155
00:07:15,210 --> 00:07:15,961
No. No!

156
00:07:16,044 --> 00:07:16,878
How long since you
have seen or heard

157
00:07:16,962 --> 00:07:17,754
from this Jack Burns?

158
00:07:17,837 --> 00:07:19,214
Well, I don't know.
I don't remember!

159
00:07:19,297 --> 00:07:20,465
You bet she doesn't remember,

160
00:07:20,548 --> 00:07:24,094
because there isn't any Jack
Burns and there never was.

161
00:07:24,177 --> 00:07:26,012
That was an alias for Jim Torrence,

162
00:07:26,096 --> 00:07:28,139
and it was Torrence who was
to have met you that night

163
00:07:28,223 --> 00:07:30,433
after your charming little
plot to kill your husband

164
00:07:30,517 --> 00:07:31,518
had been duly executed.

165
00:07:31,601 --> 00:07:32,894
It's not true! It's not true!

166
00:07:32,978 --> 00:07:34,896
I have bad news
for you, Mrs. Williams.

167
00:07:34,980 --> 00:07:36,523
I can prove it's true.

168
00:07:36,606 --> 00:07:39,985
These pajamas, these
letters, this picture,

169
00:07:40,068 --> 00:07:42,570
all of which you
identified for the court,

170
00:07:42,654 --> 00:07:44,948
were found in this suitcase,

171
00:07:45,824 --> 00:07:47,909
which is full of the clothes
and personal belongings

172
00:07:47,993 --> 00:07:50,704
of Mr. James Torrence.

173
00:07:50,787 --> 00:07:52,622
And the suitcase was
found in the baggage room

174
00:07:52,706 --> 00:07:55,500
of the airport hotel, where
it's been held since June 9th,

175
00:07:55,583 --> 00:07:57,794
and it says on this tag,

176
00:07:59,087 --> 00:08:00,000
in large print, "hold for Jack Burns."
